  "text": "The potential of these tools resides in the dialectic affordance of social interaction. They allow students to interact with students who are inherently more or less knowledgeable in supporting the co-construction of knowledge (e.g. [CITATION_1] Note: As previously described in [CITATION_2] 6 T. Campbell et al.",
